.help nsheaders November2011 gemini.gnirs
.ih
NAME
.nf
nsheaders -- Header keywords used in the gemini.gnirs package
.fi
.ih
USAGE
nsheaders instrument
.ih
PARAMETERS
.ls instrument = "gnirs"
The instrument name to load.  A file from \fIdirectory\fR having the
name of the instrument give, and the extension ".dat" is executed
within the cl.  This script should define values for the header
parameters listed below (it may also define a few other
instrument-specific values for the gemini.gnirs package).
.le
.ls directory = "gnirs$data"
A path to a directory where the \fIinstrument\fR-specific scripts are found. 
.le
.ls logfile = ""
Name of logfile.  The GNIRS package logfile "gnirs.log" is used by default.
.le
.ls verbose = no
Generate additional output in the log?
.le
.ls sci_ext
Name of science extension
.le
.ls var_ext
Name of variance extension
.le
.ls dq_ext
Name of data quality extension
.le
.ls key_instrument
Header keyword for instrument name.
.le
.ls key_bias
Header keyword for detector bias (V)
.le
.ls key_ron
Header keyword for read noise (e-)
.le
.ls key_gain
Header keyword for gain (e-/ADU)
.le
.ls key_sat
Header keyword for saturation (ADU)
.le
.ls key_nonlinear
Header keyword for non-linear regime (ADU)
.le
.ls key_arrayid
Header keyword for array ID
.le
.ls key_filter
Header keyword for filter
.le
.ls key_decker
Header keyword for decker
.le
.ls key_slit
Header keyword for slit
.le
.ls key_prism
Header keyword for prism
.le
.ls key_order
Header keyword for storing spectral order
.le
.ls key_ndavgs
Header keyword for digital averages
.le
.ls key_coadds
Header keyword for number of co-adds
.le
.ls key_lnrs
Header keyword for number of non-destructive reads
.le
.ls key_camera
Header keyword for camera
.le
.ls key_grating
Header keyword for grating
.le
.ls key_fpmask
Header keyword for focal plane mask (slit)
.le
.ls key_dispaxis
Header keyword for dispersion axis
.le
.ls key_wave
Header keyword for central grating wavelength
.le
.ls key_delta
Header keyword for linear dispersion
.le
.ls key_waveorder
Header keyword for grating wavelength order
.le
.ls key_cradius
Header keyword for wavelength cal search radius
.le
.ls key_exptime 
Header keyword for exposure time
.le
.ls key_section 
Header keyword for image section(s) to cut
.le
.ls key_cut_section
Header keyword for image section that was cut
.le
.ls key_pixscale
Header keyword for pixel scale
.le
.ls key_wavevar
Header keyword for nsappwave variable value
.le
.ls key_dark
Header keyword to identify darks
.le
.ls val_dark
Substring to match against dark header value
.le
.ls key_xoff
Header keyword for storing gemoffsetlist x offset (in arcsec)
.le
.ls key_yoff
Header keyword for storing gemoffsetlist y offset (in arcsec)
.le
.ls key_date
Header keyword for date of observation
.le
.ls key_time
Header keyword for time of observation
.le
.ls key_airmass
Header keyword for airmass
.le
.ls key_mode
Header keyword for reduction mode (value will be LS, IFU, or XD)
.le
.ls key_obstype
Header keyword for observation type
.le
.ls status = 0
This flag is non-zero after execution of NSHEADERS if a fatal error
was encountered.
.le
.ih
DESCRIPTION
NSHEADERS does not process any data.  It exists mainly as a source of
header keywords for the other tasks in the GEMINI.GNIRS package.  This
task must be run once upon loading the GNIRS package, before other ns*
tasks are executed.
.sp
The scripts used to set the header values for a particular instrument
may also be used to configure other task parameters for that
instrument.
.ih
EXAMPLE
1. Configure the package for use with the GNIRS instrument.
.sp
.nf
   ge> nsheader gnirs
.fi
.ih
